\b \cf3 MIDI Features and More\

\b0 \cf0 FretPet uses CoreMIDI to provide a MIDI source for external synthesizers and MIDI-aware software. You can use the 
\b GarageBand
\b0  synthesizer as an output to produce richer sounds than QuickTime. You can record with GarageBand as well, though 
\i synchronization is currently an issue
\i0 . Software synthesizers like Absynth and FM7 sound really impressive when FretPet is used as a controller.\
\

\b \cf3 The User Manual\

\b0 \cf0 The FretPet website includes a comprehensive HTML manual to get you started using FretPet. To read the manual just select 
\b FretPet Manual
\b0  from the 
\b Help
\b0  menu.\

