Sample Documents\

\b0 \cf0 FretPet no longer includes sample documents, but you can get them by downloading the "FretPet Extras" package from the FretPet website. There you'll also find the latest information about the current release. Just choose 
\b FretPet Website
\b0  from FretPet's 
\b Help
\b0  menu.\
\
The FretPet website has a 
\b Samples
\b0  page where I occasionally post new mixes made using FretPet with GarageBand and other synthesizers. These demonstrate that you can get some pretty great results with advanced synthesizers like GarageBand and Absynth. I recommend you check them out.\
\
You can also 
\b Subscribe to The Petcast
\b0  to hear new samples as they are posted!\
\

\b \cf3 Custom Guitar Images\

\b0 \cf0 You can now completely customize the Guitar Palette appearance, including the dots, the bracket, the playback animation, and the cursor.\
\
Before you can begin you'll need to download the "FretPet Extras" package from the website. Select "FretPet Website" from the FretPet "Help" menu to go there.\
\
In the "FretPet Extras" package you'll find a bundle named 
\b Example.guitar
\b0  which you can modify to make your own guitar themes for FretPet. Use 
\b Show Package Contents
\b0  to get inside the guitar bundle. Examine the 
\b Info.plist
\b0  file and the items in 
\b Resources
\b0  and you should have a good idea how to proceed. Guitar bundles should be placed in the 
\b ~/Library/Application Support/FretPet
\b0  folder so FretPet can find and use them.\
\
If you make a guitar theme you particularly like please feel free to send it my way and I will post it on the FretPet website for the community to use and enjoy.\
